boss /bɒs/

(bossing,bossed,bosses) 

1. N-COUNT Your boss is the person in charge of the organization or department where you work. 老板 

例： He cannot stand his boss. 他受不了他的老板。 

2. N-COUNT If you are the boss in a group or relationship, you are the person who makes all the decisions. 头儿 [非正式] 

例： He thinks he's the boss. 他自以为是头儿。 

3. V to employ, supervise, or be in charge of 雇佣; 监督; 负责 

4. V-T If you say that someone bosses you, you mean that they keep telling you what to do in a way that is irritating. 支使 

例： We cannot boss them into doing more. 我们不能再支使他们干其他事了。 

5. PHRASAL VERB Boss around means the same as . 支使 

例： He started bossing people around. 他开始支使大家了。 

6. N a knob, stud, or other circular rounded protuberance, esp an ornamental one on a vault, a ceiling, or a shield (穹顶、天花板等上的)圆形凸饰 

7. N a calf or cow 牛犊; 奶牛

